.NET Framework 3.5.name: SDK_SimBoundaries
.NET Framework 3.5.summary: The Sim Boundaries SDK script provides dummy functions for the play area boundaries.

methods.name: GetDrawAtRuntime()
methods.summary: The GetDrawAtRuntime method returns whether the given play area drawn border is being displayed.
methods.returns: Returns true if the drawn border is being displayed.

methods.name: GetPlayArea()
methods.summary: The GetPlayArea method returns the Transform of the object that is used to represent the play area in the scene.
methods.returns: A transform of the object representing the play area in the scene.

methods.name: GetPlayAreaBorderThickness()
methods.summary: The GetPlayAreaBorderThickness returns the thickness of the drawn border for the given play area.

methods.name: GetPlayAreaVertices()
methods.summary: The GetPlayAreaVertices method returns the points of the play area boundaries.
methods.returns: A Vector3 array of the points in the scene that represent the play area boundaries.

methods.name: InitBoundaries()
methods.summary: The InitBoundaries method is run on start of scene and can be used to initialse anything on game start.

methods.name: IsPlayAreaSizeCalibrated()
methods.summary: The IsPlayAreaSizeCalibrated method returns whether the given play area size has been auto calibrated by external sensors.
methods.returns: Returns true if the play area size has been auto calibrated and set by external sensors.

methods.name: SetDrawAtRuntime(bool value)
methods.summary: The SetDrawAtRuntime method sets whether the given play area drawn border should be displayed at runtime.

params.value: The state of whether the drawn border should be displayed or not.
